# Worktree Isolation

- Do not implement code changes directly in the host checkout when it may contain unrelated edits or concurrent agent work.
- Start each implementation task in an isolated git worktree on a dedicated branch.
- Prefer Cursor isolated runners/worktree-backed execution when available before touching repository files.
- Keep host checkout read-only for exploration, review, and context gathering.
- Only include task-related files in commits and pull requests from the isolated branch.

## Expected Workflow

1. Create or enter a dedicated worktree for the task branch.
2. Implement, test, and commit inside that isolated worktree only.
3. Push branch and open PR from the isolated worktree.
4. Avoid mixing changes from parallel efforts.
